---
/**
 * context-engineering/0007 · Figure 5 — Module 3 "The self-correcting loop".
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the
 * footnote <sup>). Carries its own <defs> for the arrowhead markers the shared
 * top-of-body <svg> provided in the source.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 230"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A loop: retrieve, grade the documents; if good answer, if bad re-retrieve or fall back to web search, then critique the draft and finalize."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwM"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#b5179e"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Retrieve &rarr; grade &rarr; (good? answer : re-retrieve) &rarr; critique &rarr;
            finalize</text
        >
        <!-- retrieve -->
        <rect x="40" y="44" width="120" height="40" rx="8" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"
        ></rect><text
            x="100"
            y="68"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#b5179e">Retrieve</text
        >
        <!-- grade -->
        <rect x="220" y="44" width="120" height="40" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#111110"
        ></rect><text
            x="280"
            y="62"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">Grade docs</text
        ><text x="280" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >relevant enough?</text
        >
        <line x1="160" y1="64" x2="218" y2="64" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <!-- good -> draft -->
        <rect x="400" y="44" width="120" height="40" rx="8" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text
            x="460"
            y="68"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#2f5d3a">Draft answer</text
        >
        <line x1="340" y1="64" x2="398" y2="64" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <text x="369" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#2f5d3a">good</text>
        <!-- bad -> fallback -->
        <rect x="220" y="120" width="120" height="40" rx="8" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"
        ></rect><text
            x="280"
            y="138"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#9a2417">Re-retrieve /</text
        ><text x="280" y="151" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >web fallback</text
        >
        <line x1="280" y1="84" x2="280" y2="118" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <text x="296" y="104" font-size="8" fill="#9a2417">low quality</text>
        <line x1="220" y1="140" x2="100" y2="140" stroke="#9a2417"></line><line
            x1="100"
            y1="140"
            x2="100"
            y2="86"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <!-- critique -->
        <rect x="400" y="120" width="120" height="40" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#111110"
        ></rect><text
            x="460"
            y="138"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">Critique draft</text
        ><text x="460" y="152" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >grounded? revise?</text
        >
        <line x1="460" y1="84" x2="460" y2="118" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <!-- finalize -->
        <rect
            x="400"
            y="186"
            width="120"
            height="34"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect><text
            x="460"
            y="207"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="10"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#b5179e">Finalize</text
        >
        <line x1="460" y1="160" x2="460" y2="184" stroke="#b5179e" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <!-- critique loop back -->
        <line x1="400" y1="150" x2="350" y2="150" stroke="#6b675f"></line><line
            x1="350"
            y1="150"
            x2="350"
            y2="170"
            stroke="#6b675f"></line><line x1="350" y1="170" x2="100" y2="170" stroke="#6b675f"
        ></line><line x1="100" y1="170" x2="100" y2="86" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
        ></line>
        <text x="225" y="184" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >not grounded &rarr; retrieve again</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Static RAG runs left-to-right once. Agentic RAG adds the red and grey return paths: bad docs
        trigger re-retrieval or a web fallback, and an ungrounded draft is sent back for another
        pass before anything reaches the user.<sup><a href="#s3" id="r4">3</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
